In this article, President Trump welcomes President Mauricio Macri of Argentina to the Oval Office. Trump expresses his friendship with Macri and his belief that Macri will be a great president for Argentina. They discuss the possibility of allowing Argentine lemons into the United States and the current situation in Venezuela. Trump also mentions his decision to renegotiate NAFTA after being asked by the presidents of Mexico and Canada. He states that if a fair deal cannot be reached, he will terminate NAFTA. Trump expresses sadness over the situation in Venezuela.